<br>
 I know it is your company but instead of taking money from people who spend it on playing EQ ,to put towards Planetside, SWG, EQ2 or whatever crazy things is being done with it. Games some of us never intend or want to play, and put it towards making EQ better. <br>
<br>
 I do think necessary EQ is on the back burner so to speak, the right money isnt being given to the game like it should and it is spread around various other projects, spreading your resources and income to thin. Even though, EQ is the game producing the revenue it is getting neglected in order to pay for countless other projects, most of them not EQ.<br>
<br>
 The extra money will pay to hire more GMs which EQ really needs, more devs, designers and people that can finish the product instead of half-assed attempt. I know it is logical to put some of the earnings toward new projects but not at a point the game that makes the money is neglected.<br>
<br>
 Some may disagree but in my opinion EQ is being neglected, in the past it was spoiled. Was it the best back then? No, but not near as bad as now and some are noticing and leaving, thus cutting your pool of profits down overall. I dont claim to be a professional and I maybe just talking out my ass but right now it seems EQ does not recieve the attention it should. For whatever reason things have changed, more money allocated to it, I think would help. Just my 2cp though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=c0ren>C0REN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/03 11:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Back Burner&quot;</span><hr size=1> 1) Buy a pocket calculater. Yes, I'm not kidding. If ALL your developers missed elementary school and have trouble dividing &quot;max. Raid = 78&quot; by &quot;trials ín PoTa = 5&quot; and get &quot;people per trial = 18&quot; as result, they REALLY need this pocket calculater. Or elementary school. (Or do you really just hired 100 monkeys?)<br>
<br>
2) Give us the feeling that you care. This thread had various ideas. But the base problem is all the same: You seem to give a flying fuck about what the playerbase thinks. This thread is no different btw., Absor did NOT post &quot;What do you think is the problem?&quot; but more &quot;We will try to find out by patching/nerfing in the next months what could be the problem and maybe we stumble over it and then we will bother to ask you if you agree with us.&quot; I cancelled this friday - on the day Furor's ultimatum run out. I did not cancel because I wanted some drastic changes. I cancelled because the only reaction this person got (and we're talking of a very public person which seems to hit the nerve of quite a share of the playerbase) was a &quot;/rude&quot;: You congratulated Afterlife (rumors say your favourite hatchling) on eqlive for finally beating the Rathe cockblock, when you finally unblocked it. I did not expect something like a &quot;We will obey, Mr. Furor.&quot; But I DID expect some &quot;We are aware that the Rathe encounter was majorly fucked up and we are sorry. We will from now engage in a dialog between the major guild's leaders to avoid annoying things like this happening again in the future. We will post if there is some major disagreement and what and why our position is.&quot;<br>
<br>
3) Fire all GMs. And hire some with some ethical and moral standards. When I read that GMs spawned mobs in PoTa to avoid that people, who work around <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>obviously broken</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> content, reach their goal and instead wipe, I'm speechless. Oh, and fire all developers that are touchy when their content gets beaten by less than the number that was planned for event XYZ.<br>
<br>
4) Give old models a horse. I don't want your Luclin models, they are ugly. I just want a mount. I don't want to say goodbye to the model I grew up with and trade it for a model which in my opinion not even remotely resembles any similarities.<br>
<br>
5) You gave the wizard class a major part of nerf bat hits in the last year. But even in general your usage of the nerf bat did show an IQ of sliced bread - dry. Stop going overboard. And don't wait with nerfs until all your GMs' favorite players are done with that part.<br>
<br>
6) Your definition of exploit is broken in that it doesn't allow to determine clearly if something is an exploit. Fix the definition. Also, please put up a list of all known exploits. Give the playerbase some days to get aware of it. THEN you may suspend accordingly. Currently this stupid guessworking and if-the-GM-is-in-the-mood-it's-ok sucks nuts. This board has seen more than one discussion if something is an exploit. Best example is the Workaround-without-raid-GFlux for the Concussion quest.<br>
<br>
7) Stop to break promises over and over and over. Don't promise if you are not sure and if you ARE sure, realize that promise in a short timeframe. I don't give a flying fuck if feature X is planned if it isn't in in less than let's say three month. Much less than two years.<br>
